Demonstrate clustering process on given dataset using simple k- means
Aim: To demonstrate the clustering process on a dataset using the K-Means algorithm in WEKA and group
similar data instances into clusters.
Tools:
Software: Weka (Waikato Environment for Knowledge Analysis).
Operating System: Windows / Linux
 Algorithm Used: K-Means Clustering (SimpleKMeans in WEKA)
Dataset Used:
 The dataset used is “soybean.arff” taken from the data repository of WEKA.
 The Soybean Dataset contains information about soybean plant diseases and their symptoms. Each
record represents a soybean plant observation with different conditions.
 This dataset is commonly used to apply machine learning algorithms such as SimpleKMeans, Decision
Trees (J48/ID3), and Naïve Bayes. In this experiment, it is used to perform clustering using
SimpleKMeans with 4 clusters and Manhattan distance.
