Data Mining Page No.: 44
Procedure:
Step 1: Start WEKA
 Open the WEKA tool.
 Click on Explorer.
Step 2: Load the Dataset
 Go to the Preprocess tab.
 Click Open File.
 Select the dataset soybean.arff.
 Click Open.
Step 3: Verify Dataset
 Check that all instances and attributes are loaded correctly.
 Observe dataset information in the Preprocess panel.
Date: Roll No.:
Data Mining Page No.: 45
Step 4: Move to Cluster Tab
 Click on the Cluster tab.
Step 5: Choose Clustering Algorithm
 Click Choose.
 Select SimpleKMeans.

Step 6: Set Algorithm Parameters
 Set Number of Clusters (K) = 4.
 Set Distance Function = Manhattan Distance.

Date: Roll No.:
Data Mining Page No.: 46
Step 7: Set Cluster Mode
 Under Cluster mode, select Use training set.
 From the available options, select Use training set.
 This option tells WEKA to perform clustering using the same dataset that was loaded earlier.
Step 8: Run the Algorithm
 Click Start.
 Wait for WEKA to process the dataset.
Step 9: Viewing the Results
After execution, WEKA displays the clustering results including:
 Clustering model
Date: Roll No.:
